also know the code statement and that you need to do a data step after (code only submits model information) and difference between ALL the different scoring methods - proc plm, proc logistic (inmodel/outmodel options, score statement, code statement).

How is this for a summary?
Proc GLM/GLMSelect can "Store" models
Proc Logistic:
     Outputs logits by default
     Score option outputs probabilities
     Outmodel can save model parms
     Inmodel can use model parms
     Code statement outputs model as a data step
Proc Score: Outputs logits by default
Proc PLM: 
     Outputs logits by default
     ILINK option outputs probabilities
     Can "Restore" models that were "Store"d
     Code option can save models as a data statement.
yes that is perfect!!! don't forget the code statement in PROC LOGISTIC (that was another one on the test). Also with proc plm you cannot use data= and restore= (you can only use restore= just fyi)
another good tip Caroline! I updated my post above.

Are you referring to procsurveyselect? I believe the out= statement will output the sample of the selected observations. The Outall= option will output the all of the observations and create a flag variable that indicates the samples that were selected for the training data set.
